# Route Title And Metadata

When creating or changing a page, layout, or route:

- Verify what the browser tab title will be on success, loading, empty, and failure states.
- Prefer route-specific, user-readable titles. Never leak raw error labels like `Error:` into tab titles.
- For dynamic routes, make fallback titles generic and branded if the real resource title is unavailable.
- If metadata depends on a fetch, use a stable absolute URL on the server so title generation does not fail due to relative-path or environment issues.
- Check `title`, `description`, and any Open Graph or Twitter metadata together so previews and browser tabs stay consistent.
